Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

When hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%grams} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the mushrooms are frying, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chicken stock paste{10%grams}, @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%ml}.

> Add less 'Nduja if you'd prefer things milder.

Simmer the sauce until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

Add the @Parma ham & Parmigiano Reggiano filled pasta{250%grams} and cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and gently stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once your sauce has thickened, stir the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} through the sauce until melted. Drain the @burrata{125%grams}, then carefully halve it.

Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with more salt, pepper and sugar to taste.

Gently stir your filled pasta through the sauce and share between your serving bowls.

Top with the burrata halves and @wild rocket{20%grams} and drizzle some @olive oil{} over the leaves to finish.

Enjoy!